init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the â€œLost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Your children are now living in a world where they are all immortal, but they are all sterile.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But now, it is clear that the real culprit was the drug.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are angry at the government for making them get the drug, and they are angry at the scientists for creating the drug in the first place.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They feel that their lives are not worth living anymore.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She is able to create a drug that reverses the effects of the original drug.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She is able to reverse the sterilization effects of the original drug, but she is unable to reverse the aging effects.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The men are devastated because their wives look like their grandmothers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world is now in a race to create a new generation of babies.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Women who had been barren for decades are now able to conceive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world is in a frenzy of baby making.
